dcterms:description: The KUMAR dataset consists of 30 WSI training images and 14 test images of 1000 × 1000 pixels with corresponding labels for tissue and cancer type (Breast, Kidney, Liver, Prostate, Bladder, Colon, and Stomach). It is used for evaluating segmentation performance.
dcterms:title: KUMAR dataset

dcterms:description: A proprietary collection of Kidney Transplant Pathology WSI slides with an average resolution of 30000 × 30000 per slide. The dataset includes annotated patches classified as kidney cortex, along with tabular data of patient outcomes and history of creatinine scores.
dcterms:title: Kidney Transplant Pathology dataset
